-- ============================================================
-- 098: Laborie leaf analyses — NviroTek WO 197378:251823 (2026-03-10)
-- ============================================================
-- 24 leaf-analysis samples from NviroTek Labs (Hartbeespoort), reported
-- 2026-03-13 against samples received 2026-03-10. Macros stored as %,
-- trace elements as mg/kg, matching fertasa_leaf_norms unit convention.
--
-- 25 samples on the lab report; 1 skipped because the block doesn't
-- exist on Laborie:
--   - Blok 10A (Citrus, sample L14-9064) — no matching field on the
--     farm. Likely the user has a 10A on the farm not yet entered;
--     re-run a single-row insert once the block is created.
--
-- Important caveats embedded in each row's notes:
--   - Lab note: "Leaves could not be washed". Cu and Fe surface
--     residues from spray programmes inflate trace-element readings,
--     especially on citrus (Cu 296-548 mg/kg vs typical sufficient
--     5-25; Fe 222-440 vs typical 50-150). Treat citrus Cu/Fe as
--     unreliable for the leaf engine until a re-sample is taken with
--     washed leaves.
--   - Mo reported as <1 mg/kg (below limit of detection) on every
--     sample. Stored as null in the values JSON rather than 0.5 or
--     <1 — the leaf engine handles missing keys gracefully.
-- ============================================================

BEGIN;

